#: ../../C/C-plus-plus.rst:5
msgid "C++"
msgstr "C++"

#: ../../C/C-plus-plus.rst:7
msgid "/C'·pluhs·pluhs/, n\\."
msgstr "/C'·pluhs·pluhs/, 名詞"

#: ../../C/C-plus-plus.rst:9
msgid ""
"Designed by Bjarne Stroustrup of AT&T Bell Labs as a successor to "
":ref:`C`\\. Now one of the :ref:`languages-of-choice`\\, although many "
"hackers still grumble that it is the successor to either Algol 68 or Ada "
"(depending on generation), and a prime example of :ref:`second-system-"
"effect`\\. Almost anything that can be done in any language can be done in "
"C++, but it requires a :ref:`language-lawyer` to know what is and what is "
"not legal — the design is *almost* too large to hold in even hackers' heads."
" Much of the :ref:`cruft` results from C++'s attempt to be backward "
"compatible with C. Stroustrup himself has said in his retrospective book "
"*The Design and Evolution of C++* (p. 207), \"Within C++, there is a much "
"smaller and cleaner language struggling to get out.\" [Many hackers would "
"now add \"Yes, and it's called :ref:`Java`\\\" —ESR]"
msgstr ""
"AT&Tベル研究所のBjarne Stroustrupによって\\ :ref:`C`\\ の後継として設計されました。今や\\ "
":ref:`languages-of-choice`\\ の一つですが、多くのハッカーは依然として、これはAlgol "
"68かAda(世代によります)のどちらかの後継であり、\\ :ref:`second-system-effect`\\ "
"の典型例だと不満を漏らしています。どんな言語でできることもほとんどすべてC++でできますが、何が合法で何がそうでないかを知るには\\ "
":ref:`language-lawyer`\\ が必要です——その設計はハッカーの頭にすら収まりきらない\\ *ほど*\\ 大きいのです。\\ "
":ref:`cruft`\\ の多くは、C++がCとの後方互換性を保とうとした結果です。Stroustrup自身、回顧録『The Design and "
"Evolution of "
"C++』(207ページ)の中で「C++の中には、外に出ようともがいている、はるかに小さくきれいな言語がある」と述べています。[多くのハッカーは今ならこう付け加えるでしょう。「そう、それは\\"
" :ref:`Java`\\ と呼ばれている」——ESR]"

#: ../../C/C-plus-plus.rst:19
msgid "Nowadays we say this of C++."
msgstr "今日われわれはこれをC++について言うのです。"
